    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        
            <p>The range of <i>Penstemon newberryi</i> includes the Northern California Coast Ranges (M261B) and Southern Cascades (M261D).</p>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Klamath Mountains</b> (M261Ad, Ag, Ai-k, Ap, At-u). Stands of var. <i>berryi</i> occur on glaciated rocky slope throughout the higher portions of the sections, including those at Rock Creek Butte and Sugar Creek RNAs (Cheng 2004).</li>
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Ee, Eh, Ej-k, Em-r, Et-u). Stands of var. <i>newberryi</i> at Harvey Hall RNA (Taylor 1984) and in Yosemite National Park (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b) are at high elevation limits of the alliance. The alliance is widespread on exposed granitic and metamorphic outcrops throughout the subalpine and lower alpine zones of Yosemite National Park. Stands intergrade with tree-sized or krummholz stands of <i>Pinus contorta</i> ssp. <i>murrayana</i> alliance on sheltered sites or on more highly fractured substrates where more soil accumulates in rock crevices.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Most stands are remote and relatively safe from human impact. However, some noticeable stands exist along highway road cuts and trails. </div>
</div>

    

    

    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
